    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CYLINDER HEAD INSPECTION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
            <title>INSPECT FOR WARPAGE</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Cylinder head condition must be evaluated by inspecting for warpage, thickness, cracks or
                        valve leakage.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Using a straightedge and feeler gauge, check the cylinder head gasket surface for warpage utilizing
                the checking pattern shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_51.xml" xrefid="ef4150416">4.16</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                . If specifications are
                <emph type="bold">NOT</emph>
                met check head thickness prior to resurfacing. The minimum deck-to-deck dimension must be maintained
                after resurfacing.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
